The article discusses the decline in inflation as a sign of progress, but acknowledges that more work needs to be done. The report shows a decrease in annual inflation and average monthly core inflation, but inflation is still considered too high due to price hikes. Tackling inflation is seen as a top economic priority, with plans to give The Federal Reserve the independence it needs to lower costs for families and reduce the federal deficit. However, Congressional Republicans have a different economic plan that involves increasing taxes on working families and potentially cutting programs like Social Security and Medicare. The article argues that this is not the right approach to achieve stable and steady growth for working families.